Class TigerHelpers.IMUData

java.lang.Object
com.titaniumtigers4829.TigerHelpers.IMUData
Enclosing class:
TigerHelpers
public static class TigerHelpers.IMUData extends Object
Encapsulates the state of an internal Limelight IMU. This includes gyro and accelerometer data.

    • IMUData

      public IMUData(double robotYaw, double roll, double pitch, double yaw, double gyroX, double gyroY, double gyroZ, double accelX, double accelY, double accelZ)
      Initializes an IMUData object with the provided IMU data array.
      Parameters:
      robotYaw - The yaw of the robot in degrees
      roll - The roll of the robot in degrees
      pitch - The pitch of the robot in degrees
      yaw - The yaw of the IMU in degrees
      gyroX - The x-axis gyro value in degrees per second
      gyroY - The y-axis gyro value in degrees per second
      gyroZ - The z-axis gyro value in degrees per second TODO: figure out what units the accelerometer values are in (maybe Gs?)
      accelX - The x-axis accelerometer value in meters per second squared
      accelY - The y-axis accelerometer value in meters per second squared
      accelZ - The z-axis accelerometer value in meters per second squared
